1
00:00:07,380 --> 00:00:17,410

2
00:00:17,410 --> 00:00:22,480
 'Pursue Love' - Chen Zhuo Xuan

3
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:27,060
♫  Don't be afraid, no matter how long the journey  ♫

4
00:00:29,580 --> 00:00:34,900
♫  Love embraces gentleness and care  ♫

5
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:41,540
♫  Those scars will eventually heal and turn into the blossoms gathering along time's journey  ♫

6
00:00:41,540 --> 00:00:48,390
♫  Eventually, someone will take them away for you  ♫

7
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,640
♫  Don't feel lonely moving on  ♫

8
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:56,060
♫  Let time in on your story  ♫

9
00:00:56,060 --> 00:01:03,220
♫  Expect a soft ray of light in response  ♫

10
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,700
♫  May you find her amidst the crowd  ♫

11
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:10,280
♫  May you find joy in simplicity  ♫

12
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:17,380
♫  Even though you know life is filled with regrets  ♫

13
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:23,820
♫  May you always carry your passion every Winter and Summer  ♫

14
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:25,980

15
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:29,980

16
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:37,680
But compared to an exciting life, what I prefer is a calm and lasting one.

17
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:41,220
Well, you don't have to push yourself too hard.

18
00:01:41,220 --> 00:01:43,620
Just relax and be yourself.

19
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:46,140
But I don't have time for that.

20
00:01:46,140 --> 00:01:47,800
Why?

21
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,900
I... I need to earn money to support my family.

22
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:56,140
My dad passed away and my mom retired.

23
00:01:56,140 --> 00:01:58,040
I'm the only one supporting the family.

24
00:01:58,040 --> 00:02:03,260
I have to take care of my mom's pension and handle our loans.

25
00:02:06,180 --> 00:02:10,030
How can a little person like you have so much to worry about?

26
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:11,480
I really wish I had an iron.

27
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:14,220
So next time you frown, I can smooth out the wrinkles.

28
00:02:14,220 --> 00:02:18,980
I don't want my junior to look like a little old lady at such a young age.

29
00:02:18,980 --> 00:02:21,000
Then I have to thank you first.

30
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,160
This way, I can save some money on facial masks.

31
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:26,640
Pharmaceutical representatives earn a lot.

32
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:28,780
Do you want to consider joining my company?

33
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:30,080
Forget it.

34
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:33,160
Domestic competition is too fierce, I can't handle it.

35
00:02:37,940 --> 00:02:42,300
You must remember that I'm always behind you.

36
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:45,220
I'll always be your strongest supporter.

37
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,540
Thanks, Senior.

38
00:02:48,540 --> 00:02:53,020
You've always had your own rhythm, just like your performance earlier.

39
00:02:53,020 --> 00:02:57,660
And I can only try my best to keep up with your beat.

40
00:02:58,580 --> 00:03:02,060
Senior, keep your own rhythm.

41
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:04,600
Don't change it because of me.

42
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:16,600
I hope that one day, you'll be the CEO of China's biggest pharmaceutical company.

43
00:03:17,180 --> 00:03:22,800
Even if you're not a doctor, you can still be on Huaren Medical University's honorary alumni list, right?

44
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:26,220
Let me take this call.

45
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,940
Hello?

46
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,820

47
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:43,780
Mom, calm down first. Which hospital?

48
00:03:44,660 --> 00:03:46,460
Huaren?

49
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:50,460
It's okay. I'm on my way.

50
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:54,620
To Huaren Hospital, please.

51
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:59,540
Hello, Professor Gu.

52
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:04,860
Xiao Zhang, do you know who in our department is on duty for emergencies tonight?

53
00:04:04,860 --> 00:04:07,740
Professor He Xiaoguang and Wen Ran.

54
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:09,140
Why are you so excited?

55
00:04:09,140 --> 00:04:12,500
Guess who's coming?

56
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:14,980
Don't beat around the bush. Just tell me.

57
00:04:14,980 --> 00:04:19,280
Su Wei'an, the female student who reported Professor He and Wen Ran back then.

58
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:20,670
Really?

59
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:22,820
What a small world.

60
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:25,780
The emergency department will be quite a spectacle tonight.

61
00:04:27,220 --> 00:04:30,680
Who did you say? Su Wei'an?

62
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:33,080
Today, her relative came to our emergency department.

63
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:38,020
Professor He and Wen Ran are on duty.

64
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,620
No.

65
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,380
The tendon reflex wouldn't be hyperactive like this.

66
00:04:42,380 --> 00:04:47,060
Now, we should perform a differential diagnosis to rule out more serious illnesses.

67
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:50,300
The patient's family said that this symptom occurs regularly.

68
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:52,260
- It can go away on its own. 
 - Yes.

69
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:55,440
This is indeed just a fluctuation in the symptoms of chorea.

70
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:58,780
This is very likely to be a symptom of a new illness.

71
00:04:58,780 --> 00:05:01,460
Do you think I'm medically illiterate?

72
00:05:02,340 --> 00:05:04,700
Do you think you aren't? Who's the doctor here, you or me?

73
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:07,640
You've only learned the basics for a few days, and now you're showing off?

74
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:10,980
Wei'an, we completely understand how you feel.

75
00:05:10,980 --> 00:05:12,740
But you're not a doctor after all.

76
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:14,340
You should trust the doctor's judgment.

77
00:05:14,340 --> 00:05:16,100
The doctor said it's nothing serious.

78
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:20,180
Why would anyone wish for their relative to be seriously ill?

79
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:25,640
I've only learned the basics, but I know we should perform a differential diagnosis now.

80
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:28,300
You're sending the patient home after simply glancing at her.

81
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:31,020
Is this how a doctor should act?

82
00:05:31,020 --> 00:05:34,260
With your irresponsible attitude, it's hard for me to trust your medical ethics and skills.

83
00:05:34,260 --> 00:05:35,660
I want to see the chief doctor on duty today.

84
00:05:35,660 --> 00:05:38,240
You want to see the chief doctor? Do you think you have the right to see them?

85
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:40,120
Besides, don't use seniority to pressure me.

86
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:46,160
He Xiaoguang, if anything happens to my aunt today, I'll sue you until you can no longer be a doctor.

87
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:48,820
Do you think I can't handle you?

88
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:51,440
Security. Security!

89
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,200
- It's okay, Mom. 
 - Why don't we listen to the doctor and go home first?

90
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:54,220
- It's okay, Mom. 
 - Why don't we listen to the doctor and go home first?

91
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:57,820
Wei'an, let me make a call first. Don't worry.

92
00:05:57,820 --> 00:06:00,460
Mom, Auntie's condition is critical right now.

93
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:02,000
- This little girl is causing trouble. 
 - What are you doing?

94
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,980
- Get her out of here. 
 - What are you doing?

95
00:06:02,980 --> 00:06:04,480
- Sir, don't block me. 
 - What? 
 - What's the matter?

96
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:06,380
Don't get physical.

97
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:25,120
It's nothing, someone's causing trouble here.

98
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,380
You can go about your work, Dr. Gu.

99
00:06:26,380 --> 00:06:28,970
I'm on duty today, so I'll handle this.

100
00:06:29,420 --> 00:06:33,360
Dr. He, I was asking you what's the matter with the patient.

101
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:45,260
The patient's main complaint is stiffness in her limbs.

102
00:06:45,260 --> 00:06:50,600
Given that she has a history of high blood pressure and Huntington's disease—

103
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,400
What did you say?

104
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:55,380
Huntington's disease?

105
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:56,940
Yes.

106
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:37,420
The patient shows a positive Babinski sign. Arrange a head CT for her immediately. 
  (TN: foot reflex that leads to extension of the big toe)

107
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:39,360
Hurry.

108
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:42,880
A head CT won't show chorea.

109
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:52,940
But it can show cerebral hemorrhage.

110
00:08:05,980 --> 00:08:07,880
Dr. Gu.

111
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:12,820
You're not suspecting that I've misdiagnosed, are you?

112
00:08:12,820 --> 00:08:15,900
The patient is alert and articulate, with symmetrical facial features.

113
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:18,340
The muscle strength of her limbs is normal.

114
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:25,560
Even if she shows a positive Babinski sign, Huntington's disease itself may also present pathologically positive signs.

115
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:30,660
These are the typical fluctuations of chorea symptoms. Why are we wasting more time here?

116
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:34,080
Instead, the patient's family members are being unreasonable and causing trouble.

117
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:39,701
If her head CT shows no problems at all, then are they going to sue us for unnecessary treatment?

118
00:08:42,560 --> 00:08:47,040
Dr. He, what are the signs of Huntington's disease?

119
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:49,440
Dancing movements.

120
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:53,740
Hold on, Dr. Gu, Huntington's disease is rare.

121
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:56,840
We see very few cases among our patients.

122
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,760
Besides, this isn't my specialty.

123
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:03,600
By publicly asking me such detailed questions about it,  aren't you making it difficult for me?

124
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:08,300
Dr. He, you don't even know the specific signs of Huntington's disease.

125
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:13,640
How can you be sure that the patient's stiffness is caused by Huntington's disease?

126
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:18,000
Right now, shouldn't we rule out more serious illnesses first?

127
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:22,300
How long has the patient been like this?

128
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:25,000
More than three hours.

129
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:29,460
When she had this symptom in the past, how long did it take to resolve itself?

130
00:09:29,460 --> 00:09:31,740
- About... 
 - Within half an hour.

131
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:33,600
Yes.

132
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:40,440
Head Nurse, I'm heading to the CT room now to check the patient's results.

133
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,830
Be prepared for surgery at any time.

134
00:09:43,460 --> 00:09:45,680
She needs surgery?

135
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:48,700
Have faith in Dr. Gu.

136
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:51,540
It's okay, Wei'an.

137
00:09:51,540 --> 00:09:55,340
I'll stay with you until your aunt is better.

138
00:09:55,340 --> 00:09:57,360
Thank you, Senior.

139
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:04,700

140
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:05,820

141
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:16,700
Aneurysm clip.

142
00:10:32,820 --> 00:10:35,100
What's the patient's relationship to Su Wei'an?

143
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:38,720
According to Wei'an's mom, it's her aunt.

144
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,020
Her biological aunt?

145
00:10:40,020 --> 00:10:41,280
I think so.

146
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,960
What's wrong?

147
00:10:45,620 --> 00:10:47,540
Nothing.

148
00:10:47,540 --> 00:10:49,700

149
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:56,020
Wei'an, it's been so long, why haven't they come out yet?

150
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,240
Should you go ask?

151
00:10:57,240 --> 00:11:00,560
Mom, Gu Yunzheng is the best doctor in the Neurosurgery Department.

152
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:03,380
Trust him. Don't worry.

153
00:11:04,620 --> 00:11:07,000
Here they come.

154
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,840
Dr. Gu.

155
00:11:12,608 --> 00:11:14,848
The operation went very well.

156
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:21,640
But right now, we're still unsure about the extent of damage caused by this hemorrhage to the patient.

157
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:28,820
She may fully recover from this, but there can also be some functional impairment.

158
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:31,420
She still needs to be hospitalized for further observation.

159
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:33,900
Then when will she wake up?

160
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:37,260
It's hard to say. It depends on the patient's situation.

161
00:11:37,260 --> 00:11:39,420
We'll send her to the ICU first. 
  (T/N: Intensive Care Unit)

162
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:43,540
When her condition stabilizes, we'll transfer her to the regular ward.

163
00:11:43,540 --> 00:11:46,420
What caused this hemorrhage?

164
00:11:46,420 --> 00:11:49,580
The patient had a ruptured aneurysm.

165
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,740
Aneurysm?

166
00:11:51,740 --> 00:11:53,100
But don't worry.

167
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:56,540
We've already clipped the responsible aneurysm during the operation.

168
00:11:56,540 --> 00:11:59,460
She's no longer in danger now.

169
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:03,100
But before my aunt joined the drug trial, she did an MRA. 
  (T/N: Magnetic Resonance Angiography)

170
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:06,280
Her blood vessels were all normal. How could there be an aneurysm?

171
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:08,080
That's right.

172
00:12:08,620 --> 00:12:10,720
What drug trial?

173
00:12:11,580 --> 00:12:13,260
HDQ39.

174
00:12:13,260 --> 00:12:16,580
A specialized drug specifically for treating Huntington's disease.

175
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:24,020
It's a joint research project between Jiehui and Professor Wen Yuliang of Zhang He Hospital.

176
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:31,900
This is considered an adverse event that occurred during a drug trial.

177
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:37,600
I will communicate with Professor Wen and discuss the patient's future treatment plans with him.

178
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,580
Okay.

179
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:43,240
Dr. Gu, I guess we'll need your help with a lot of things in the future.

180
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:44,840
No problem.

181
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,720
Mom, it's late. Let the doctor go back and rest.

182
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:52,480
- Okay. 
 - Let's go back too.

183
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:54,600
Then please excuse us.

184
00:12:58,460 --> 00:13:01,780
Auntie, Wei'an, my driver is downstairs. Let me give you a ride.

185
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:03,820
It's okay, we'll call a taxi.

186
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:07,180
Yes, Xiao Du, we shouldn't trouble you anymore.

187
00:13:07,180 --> 00:13:10,060
You've been waiting with us for so long already.

188
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:12,360
It's very late,

189
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:15,140
and it's a long ride. I'll be worried.

190
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:16,620
Let's save the courtesy.

191
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:19,880
If we keep being so polite, it'll be morning soon.

192
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:23,200
Okay, thank you then.

193
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,760
- Let's go. 
 - Let's go.

194
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:25,680
Thanks, Senior.

195
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,380
Let's go.

196
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:43,840
Xiao Du,

197
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:47,780
do you know that Dr. Gu from earlier?

198
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:49,520
Do you know him well?

199
00:13:53,380 --> 00:13:57,780
I know him, but that's all. Is something the matter?

200
00:13:57,780 --> 00:14:01,180
Ah Yuan is hospitalized now.

201
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:06,060
Wouldn't it be better to have a doctor we know?

202
00:14:09,580 --> 00:14:13,400
Auntie, my father is the director of that hospital.

203
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:18,200
Other than Dr. Gu, I know all the other heads in the Neurosurgery Department.

204
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:22,360
If you need any help from them, please feel free to ask.

205
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,780
- That's wonderful. 
 - Mom.

206
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:28,380
Dr. Gu is very sincere and responsible when treating patients.

207
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:33,780
Even if you don't ask him, he'll do what a doctor should do.

208
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,160
Do you two know each other?

209
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:42,540
- They met in Laka— 
 - Dr. Gu is a professor at Huaren.

210
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:48,800
At our school, he's known for his medical skills and ethics.

211
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:50,240
You don't have to worry.

212
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:53,120
Good. That's good, then.

213
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:23,620
 The patient's main complaint is stiffness in her limbs.

214
00:15:23,620 --> 00:15:28,320
 Given that she has a history of high blood pressure and Huntington's disease...

215
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:30,440
 What's the patient's relationship to Su Wei'an?

216
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:33,340
 According to Wei'an's mom, it's her aunt.

217
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:34,505
 Her biological aunt?

218
00:15:34,505 --> 00:15:37,660
 I think so. What's wrong?

219
00:15:37,660 --> 00:15:40,500
 Huntington's disease?

220
00:15:54,940 --> 00:15:56,720
Good morning, Dr. Gu.

221
00:16:18,340 --> 00:16:20,880
Wait, Li Wantong, what are you trying to do?

222
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:23,180
You tell me.

223
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:31,260
It is said that giving a man a tie can win his heart.

224
00:16:31,260 --> 00:16:35,560
This brand is suitable for the outstanding you.

225
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:49,320
Miss Su! Long time no see.

226
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:52,460
I picked out a tie for Dr. Gu. Does it look good?

227
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,980
Yes.

228
00:16:55,980 --> 00:16:57,200
Do you want to come in?

229
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,760
No thanks.

230
00:17:09,580 --> 00:17:14,485
Gu Yunzheng, doing such a manly thing in front of me

231
00:17:14,485 --> 00:17:18,400
will only make me even more obsessed with you.

232
00:17:23,010 --> 00:17:27,560
Li Wantong and I aren't what you think.

233
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:30,420
You don't need to explain to me. I don't mind.

234
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:32,180
You're lying.

235
00:17:34,140 --> 00:17:37,020
Why are you afraid to look me in the eye right now?

236
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:44,020
Su Wei'an, do you know that your eyes and expressions can give you away?

237
00:17:54,260 --> 00:17:56,540
Can I ask you for a favor?

238
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:01,340
Can you please pretend not to know me in front of my mom?

239
00:18:01,340 --> 00:18:03,905
I don't want her to know everything about my time in Lakaya.

240
00:18:03,905 --> 00:18:08,485
Is it everything about Lakaya, or everything between us?

241
00:18:09,140 --> 00:18:12,780
Are you trying to hide it from your mom, or are you afraid Du Yuncheng will misunderstand?

242
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:22,520
Are you afraid they'll find out that you took a beating for me?

243
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:25,640
Are you afraid they'll find out we saw a night rainbow together?

244
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:28,820
Or are you afraid they'll find out we've watched the stars together?

245
00:18:29,660 --> 00:18:32,860
We've been through so much together in Lakaya.

246
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:35,260
Which one are you most afraid of them finding out about?

247
00:18:35,260 --> 00:18:37,260
All of them.

248
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:46,860
Dr. Gu, if you keep dwelling on the past, it becomes meaningless.

249
00:18:50,580 --> 00:18:52,340
